    "department": "Global Brand \u0026 MKT Center",
    "description": "Job Position: Italy Integrated Marketing Manager\n\nLocation: Amsterdam/Milan\n\n\nABOUT PLAUD INC.\n\nPlaud is building the world's most trusted AI work companion for professionals to elevate productivity and performance through note-taking solutions, loved by over 1,000,000 users worldwide since 2023. With a mission to amplify human intelligence, Plaud is building the next-generation intelligence infrastructure and interfaces to capture, extract, and utilize what you say, hear, see, and think.\n\nPlaud Inc. is a Delaware-incorporated, San Francisco-based company pushing the boundary of human–AI intelligence through a hardware–software combination. With ISO 27001, ISO 27701, GDPR, SOC 2, HIPAA, and EN 18031 compliance, Plaud is committed to the highest standards of data security and privacy protection.\n\nTo learn more about Plaud, please visit http://www.plaud.ai/https://www.plaud.ai and follow along on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/plaud_official/, X https://twitter.com/PLAUDAI, Facebook https://www.facebook.com/plaudai, LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/plaudai/?viewAsMember=true, and YouTube https://www.youtube.com/@PLAUDAI\n\n\nWHY YOU SHOULD JOIN US\n\nPlaud is building the next generation intelligence infrastructure and interfaces to capture, extract, and utilize intelligence from what people say, hear, see, and think.\n\n - Plaud is a bootstrapped, skyrocketing, profitable company with a $250M revenue run rate achieved in just three years.\n\n - Define the next-gen paradigm for human-AI interaction.\n\n - Gain exposure to cutting-edge AI for Pro tools and play a direct role in our global expansion.\n\n - Work with passionate teammates who value innovation, collaboration, and customer success.\n\n - Grow your career in a culture that champions continuous learning and fast career development.\n\n - Market-competitive compensation, global exposure, and a vibrant, creativity-fueled work atmosphere.\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO\n\n - Execute Plaud’s integrated marketing campaigns across PR, influencer, digital, retail, and DTC channels for the local market.\n\n - Localize global IMC strategies and creative assets to ensure cultural relevance and regulatory compliance.\n\n - Manage local creative, media, and PR agencies to deliver campaigns on time, on budget, and on brand.\n\n - Coordinate with HQ IMC and Product Marketing teams to align messaging, visuals, and launch timelines.\n\n - Monitor campaign performance, compile post-campaign reports, and provide actionable feedback to HQ.\n\n\nMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS\n\n - 3–5 years of experience in integrated marketing, campaign management, or brand activation, ideally in tech, SaaS, or consumer electronics.\n\n - Proven experience executing multi-channel campaigns and managing agency partners.\n\n - Strong understanding of local media, PR, and influencer landscapes.\n\n - Native-level Italian proficiency with strong English communication skills.\n\n - Highly organized, structured, and capable of managing multiple priorities.\n\n - Good at using AI tools to improve work efficiency.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n - Experience localizing global campaigns for the local market.\n\n - Familiarity with AI, SaaS, or consumer tech products.\n\n - Proficiency in AI and productivity tools (ChatGPT, Notion, Airtable, Google Workspace, Figma).\n\n - Analytical mindset with ability to interpret campaign performance and ROI.\n\n - Passion for building brand trust and storytelling in technology.\n\nDisclaimer: Plaud is and will continue to be an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, age, veteran status, disability, genetic information, or other applicable legally protected characteristics.",
